ID  - 17953943 [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17953943]
T1  - Triplet pregnancy after ovulation induction with an aromatase inhibitor
A1  - Dicken C.L.
A1  - Nakhuda G.S.
A1  - Guarnaccia M.M.
A1  - Sauer M.V.
A1  - Lobo R.A. 
Y1  - 2008//
N2  - Objective: To describe the first reported case of a triplet pregnancy subsequent to the use of an aromatase inhibitor for ovulation induction. Design(s): Case report. Setting(s): Academic medical center. Patient(s): A 32-year-old female with polycystic ovary syndrome and primary infertility. Intervention(s): Letrozole, 5 mg/day, on cycle days 2 to 6 for ovulation induction. Main Outcome Measure(s): Clinical pregnancy. Result(s): Viable triplet gestation. Conclusion(s): Use of an aromatase inhibitor for ovulation induction does not eliminate the risk for higher order multiple pregnancy. © 2008 American Society for Reproductive Medicine.
