8254. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 351359552
T1  - Dermatological problems in adolescents
A1  - George A.E. 
Y1  - 2007//
N2  - Adolescence is a phase in a child's development when significant physical and psychological changes occur before the child grows into an adult. Some of the important dermatological issues in this period include acne, dandruff and hirsutism and all of them have a linkage to the hormonal variations especially of androgens in their etiology. The various causes as well as management of these conditions are discussed.
