T1  - Endometrial carcinoma with ovarian metastases incidentally detected in a 30-year-old infertile patient - Case report
A1  - Vasiljevic M.
A1  - Prorocic M.
A1  - Vasiljevic N.
A1  - Tasic L.
A1  - Mladenko V. 
Y1  - 2007//
N2  - This is a case of invasive endometrial carcinoma with ovarian metastases incidentally detected in a 30-year-old infertile woman. The patient was asymptomatic. Carcinoma was discovered during hysteroscopy. She was submitted to surgical treatment involving total hysterectomy, bilateral salpingo- oophorectomy and dissection of the pelvic and paraaortal lymph nodes. Postoperative irradiation therapy was performed. Since treatment the patient has been well.
