ID  - 17496742 [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17496742]
T1  - Clomiphene-induced acute pancreatitis without hypertriglyceridemia
A1  - Keskin M.
A1  - Songur Y.
A1  - Isler M. 
Y1  - 2007//
N2  - Acute pancreatitis may be caused by drugs. In the literature, there are more than 260 different drugs that have been blamed for causing pancreatitis. Among these drugs, only 1 case has been reported as clomiphene-induced acute pancreatitis. However, in this single case, there was concomitant hypertrigliceridemia. We report the case of a woman who developed 2 attacks of acute pancreatitis without hypertriglyceridemia while receiving treatment with clomiphene. © Copyright 2007 Southern Society for Clinical Investigation.
