T1  - An unusual complication of thrombolysis - Bilateral retro-orbital haematomata
A1  - Ahmar W.
A1  - Mason K.
A1  - Harley N.
A1  - Hogan C. 
Y1  - 2005//
N2  - We present a case of bilateral retro-orbital haematomata following thrombolysis of pulmonary embolism in a severely haemodynamically compromised 29-year-old female. The haematomata developed two days post-thrombolysis with marked visual impairment. Visual acuity was restored following bilateral drainage of the superior aspects of the retro-orbital space.
