T1  - Ovarian enzyme activities in women with polycystic ovary syndrome
A1  - Magoffin D.A. 
Y1  - 2006//
N2  - Studies using primary ovarian tissue and cultured human theca and granulosa cells have shown that steroidogenic enzyme activities are up-regulated in theca cells in polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS). Although granulosa cells in arrested follicles in PCOS fail to express significant amounts of aromatase, there is an overexpression of 5alpha-reductase activity and premature expression of cholesterol side-chain cleavage cytochrome P450. © 2006 American Society for Reproductive Medicine.
