8423. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 43913773
ID  - 16798286 [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16798286]
T1  - Prenatal growth restraint followed by catch-up of weight: a hyperinsulinemic pathway to polycystic ovary syndrome
A1  - de Zegher F.
A1  - Ibanez L. 
Y1  - 2006//
N2  - One of the pathways to polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) starts with an early-life sequence of prenatal growth restraint followed by catch-up of weight during infancy. This sequence results by mid-childhood in a pre-PCOS state including hyperinsulinemia, a low-grade proinflammatory state, an amplified adrenarche (with or without precocious pubarche), and an adipose body composition even in the absence of obesity. This variant of pre-PCOS and PCOS responds well to intervention with metformin. © 2006 American Society for Reproductive Medicine.
