T1  - Nonclassic adrenal hyperplasia
A1  - Moran C. 
Y1  - 2006//
N2  - Among 297 women with nonclassic adrenal hyperplasia (NCAH), premature pubarche was the most common complaint in girls (87%), and the frequency of hirsutism increased progressively with age from adolescence (50%) to adulthood (70%). The frequency of spontaneous miscarriages was high in NCAH patients (20%), but it decreased significantly after treatment. © 2006 American Society for Reproductive Medicine.
