T1  - The Rahn-Otis discovery of hypoxic ventilatory decline
A1  - Severinghaus J.W. 
Y1  - 2005//
N2  - In summary, Rahn and Otis provided strong evidence related to the cause of the delay of acclimatization to high altitude as evidenced by the slow, quasi-exponential fall of alveolar PCO2 over the first several days at altitude. They correctly identified inhibiton of hypoxic ventilatory response, demonstrated the dramatic difference of hypoxic responses of acclimatized versus unacclimatized subjects, and inferred that pH in a central respiratory chemoreceptor was involved. The HVD they first identified remains only partially explained. © Mary Ann Liebert, Inc.
