T1  - An our study on hirsutism
A1  - Ruggiero A.
A1  - Sorrentino S.
A1  - Sorrentino B.
A1  - Ruggiero D.
A1  - Ruggiero G.
A1  - Elberti A. 
Y1  - 2003//
N2  - 24% of 15-20-year-old patients, subjected to our observation, is affected by hirsutism, consisting in an abnormal growth of hairs in unusual parts of the body. The etiology of hyperandrogynism is represented by adrenal tumours, ACTH hypersecretion, deficiency of adrenal enzymes and polycystic ovary syndrome. The therapy consists in changes in the diet of the patients who are often obese, and in a pharmacological therapy with antiandrogens (acetate cyproterone and ethynylestradiol; flutamide). At present, the most accepted therapy is represented by 35 mcg of ethynylestradiol combined with 2 mg of acetate cyproterone (DIANE), both combined with 50/100 mg tablets of acetate cyproterone a day for the first ten days of therapy.
