9134. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 33094799
ID  - 11964028 [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11964028]
T1  - Hirsutism of adrenal origin in adolescents: Consequences in adults
A1  - Kelestimur F. 
Y1  - 2001//
N2  - Hirsutism is a common clinical and psychological problem in women. Polycystic ovary syndrome and idiopathic hirsutism are the most common causes of hirsutism. Adrenal disorders are less common causes of hirsutism; the most common adrenal cause of hirsutism is non-classical congenital adrenal hyperplasia (NC-CAH). Hirsutism may be the presenting symptom of an adrenal carcinoma or adenoma. In this review, adrenal causes of hirsutism, the pathophysiology of the hirsutism in NC-CAH, and the treatment of hirsutism in these patients, are discussed.
