N2  - Production of transforming growth factor-beta2 mRNA in the endometrium of women with polycystic ovary syndrome decreased compared to normal and this decrease directly depends on the duration of anovulatory period (from 3 weeks to 4 months). Low production of transforming growth factor-beta2 mRNA probably contributes to the development of endometrial hyperplasia in women with polycystic ovary syndrome.
